      "writtenOn": "2020-12-14T09:30:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Currently control.crosbolt-perbuild runs tests with the following attribute expression:\n\n (\"group:crosbolt\" \u0026\u0026 crosbolt_perbuild)\n\nhttps://source.corp.google.com/chromeos_public/src/third_party/autotest/files/server/site_tests/tast/control.crosbolt-perbuild\n\nWe can modify the attribute expression to filter by android deps, i.e.\n\n (\"group:crosbolt\" \u0026\u0026 crosbolt_perbuild \u0026\u0026 !\"dep:android*\")\n\nand introduce another control file (e.g. control.crosbolt-perbuild-android) that triggers Android-related perf tests\n\n (\"group:crosbolt\" \u0026\u0026 crosbolt_perbuild \u0026\u0026 \"dep:android*\")\n\nThen we don\u0027t need to introduce the new attribute crosbolt_arc_perf_perbuild. I believe it\u0027s easier for test authors to maintain tests, because running Android perf tests separately from other perf tests are scheduling details.",
      "parentUuid": "9b46ea04_e4daf73b",
